Roam Research CLI (Go)

Usage:
  roam-cli [command]

Available Commands:
  batch        Low-level batch actions API
  block        Low-level block APIs
  completion   Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  get          Get page by title or block by uid
  help         Help about any command, help topic, or example category
  journal      Get journaling blocks from Daily Notes
  q            Execute raw datalog query
  save         Save markdown as a Roam page or under a parent block
  search       Search blocks containing all terms
  search-pages Multi-query search aggregated by page
  status       Check roam-cli credential and API connectivity status

Flags:
      --base-url string   Roam API base URL (overrides ROAM_API_BASE_URL)
      --graph string      Roam graph name (overrides ROAM_API_GRAPH)
  -h, --help              help for roam-cli
      --timeout int       Request timeout in seconds (overrides ROAM_TIMEOUT_SECONDS)
      --token string      Roam API token (overrides ROAM_API_TOKEN)
  -v, --version           version for roam-cli

Use "roam-cli [command] --help" for more information about a command.

HELP TOPICS
  datalog        Roam Research exposes a Datomic-flavored Datalog query API with Clojure built-in functions.
  exit-codes     Stable exit codes for scripting and automation.

Use "roam-cli help <topic>" for more information about a topic.

Example categories (roam-cli help <category>):
  read         Read pages, blocks, search, query, and journal
  write        Save markdown, create blocks, batch operations
  workflow     Common multi-step patterns for efficient Roam operations
  all          Show all categories
